<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,1259]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,419,224,251]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Description. Adult</emphasis>
. Described in detail and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, R. G. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D." box="[864,1310,225,251]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref69240" refString="Brown, R. G. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D. (1988) Taxonomy and ecology of the jumping plant-lice of Panama (Homoptera: Psylloidea). E. J. Brill, Scandinavian Science Press Ltd., Leiden, New York, Kopenhagen, Koln, 304 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156853988 X 00241" type="book" year="1988">Brown and Hodkinson (1988: 139–141</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Limbopsylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beeryi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Limbopsylla beeryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,1259]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,465,296,323]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fifth instar immature</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[482,568,297,324]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–21" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1855,1880]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,733,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,733,1835]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 11–21. Immature psyllids associated with Detarieae; 11–15, caudal plate; apf = additional pore fields, ocr = outer circumanal ring, ss = sectasetae; 16, 17, habitus, right body side; 18, 19, apex of tarsus with claws and tarsal arolium; 20, 21, outer circumanal ring (ocr).—11, 16, 18, Apsyllopsis mexicana; 12, 19, Colophorina tapuio sp. nov.; 13, 20, Jataiba uncigera sp. nov.; 14, 21, Mitrapsylla gloriae sp. nov.; 15, Platycorypha rostrata sp. nov.; 17, Colophorina tupi sp. nov.—Scales 11–15 = 0.2 mm; scales 16, 17 = 0.3 mm; scales 18–21 = 0.03 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669653" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3669653/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Colouration. Dirty whitish or yellowish. Eyes reddish; antennal flagellum light brown at base, getting gradually darker towards brown apex; tip of rostrum black. Tibiae and tarsi greyish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,1259]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Structure. Body 1.6–1.8 times as long as wide. Antenna 1.4–1.6 times as long as forewing pad; setae on antenna just slightly longer than flagellar diameter. Forewing pad very narrow, about 3 times as long as wide; bearing 30–40 irregularly spaced, long and medium long marginal setae, and a few short, scattered setae dorsally. Extra pore fields extending antero-dorsally to fore margin of caudal plate (
<figureCitation box="[792,873,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–21" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1855,1880]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,733,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,733,1835]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 11–21. Immature psyllids associated with Detarieae; 11–15, caudal plate; apf = additional pore fields, ocr = outer circumanal ring, ss = sectasetae; 16, 17, habitus, right body side; 18, 19, apex of tarsus with claws and tarsal arolium; 20, 21, outer circumanal ring (ocr).—11, 16, 18, Apsyllopsis mexicana; 12, 19, Colophorina tapuio sp. nov.; 13, 20, Jataiba uncigera sp. nov.; 14, 21, Mitrapsylla gloriae sp. nov.; 15, Platycorypha rostrata sp. nov.; 17, Colophorina tupi sp. nov.—Scales 11–15 = 0.2 mm; scales 16, 17 = 0.3 mm; scales 18–21 = 0.03 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669653" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3669653/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,1259]" box="[199,1317,548,576]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Measurements (in mm) and ratios (
<specimenCount box="[592,738,549,576]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="immature">4 immatures</specimenCount>
). Body length 2.28–2.52, antenna length 1.08–1.30.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,1259]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,246,585,611]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Egg</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[262,351,585,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1290,1315]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,445,1268]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,445,1271]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Eggs of psyllids associated with Detarieae; 22, Apsyllopsis mexicana; 23, Colophorina guarani sp. nov.; 24, Platycorypha amazonica sp. nov.; 25, Jataiba uncigera sp. nov.; 26, Mitrapsylla sp.—Scales 0.2 mm; 24–26 = scale 26." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3669655/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 22</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[364,395,584,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–38" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1916,1941]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,697,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,697,1896]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 27–38. Adult Macrocorsinae; 27–30, habitus, lateral view; 31–34, head, dorsal view; 35, egg; 36–38, galls.—27, 31, 35–38, Apsyllopsis mexicana; 28, 32, Colophorina tapuio sp. nov.; 29, 33, Euryconus sp. Brazil ex Dipteryx alata; 30, 34, Macrocorsa sp. Brazil.—Scales 31–34 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3669657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3669657/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">35</figureCitation>
). Orange brown, pedicel brown. Described and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, R. G. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref69240" refString="Brown, R. G. &amp; Hodkinson, I. D. (1988) Taxonomy and ecology of the jumping plant-lice of Panama (Homoptera: Psylloidea). E. J. Brill, Scandinavian Science Press Ltd., Leiden, New York, Kopenhagen, Koln, 304 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156853988 X 00241" type="book" year="1988">Brown and Hodkinson (1988: 139–141</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName box="[294,509,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Psyllidae" genus="Limbopsylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beeryi">
<emphasis box="[294,509,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Limbopsylla beeryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
